The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically multiterminal source coding models involving successive refinement. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses cooperation between decoders, which could fall under the cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.SI (Signal Processing) sub-categories. The use of coding schemes and algorithms suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper introduces and solves dual-channel coding scenarios, which could fall under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
